{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fa337bfc-31d8-46b7-b982-4864f424eca6","content":"No files found in the working directory. I'll provide the solution directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` root element, pointing to your ViewModel:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"36\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n**Key change:** the `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` attribute. This tells the XAML compiler to resolve every `{Binding}` in scope against that type at **compile time**.\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\n**1. Enable strict mode** — add this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Treat binding failures as build errors, not warnings -->\n  <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**2. What this catches:** if you typo a property (e.g., `{Binding Themee}`), the build will **fail** with an error like:\n\n```\nXC0045: Binding: Property \"Themee\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\".\n```\n\nWithout `x:DataType`, this would silently fail at runtime.\n\n**3. Opt out locally** when needed (e.g., binding to a non-typed parent context):\n\n```xml\n<!-- Disable compiled binding for this one element -->\n<Label Text=\"{Binding SomeOtherProp}\" x:DataType=\"{x:Null}\" />\n```\n\n**Summary:** add `x:DataType` → bindings resolve at compile time → enable `MauiStrictXamlCompilation` → typos become build errors instead of silent runtime failures.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8f1168d3-e62b-4349-84e3-fc4c7f44f600","outputTokens":680,"requestId":"1423:1287AC:6E7C20C:76BBF36:6A03CBBB"},"id":"dc1180c8-d525-4e78-9676-bc7ff7cc5b9f","timestamp":"2026-05-13T00:54:33.004Z","parentId":"371c22f1-d906-45ef-8c1d-9c7b2ca67db9"}
